-- 
German Retirement Age Hit Record High in 2010, Bild Reports

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-07-27T05:36:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/german-retirement-age-hit-record-high-in-2010-bild-reports.html
The average retirement age of German
workers rose to the highest on record last year,  Bild-Zeitung 
reported, citing a survey from the country’s Deutsche
Rentenversicherung Bund pension fund agency.  Men retired at 63.8 years on average, up from 63.5 years a
year earlier, while women’s retirement age rose to 63.3 years
from 62.9 years, according to the report. Those were the highest
values since records for a re-unified  Germany  began in 1993,
Bild said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
